HEADWORD: Undine
<hw>Un*dine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>undine</ets>, or F. <ets>ondin</ets>, <ets>ondine</ets>, from L.
<ets>unda</ets> a wave, water.]</ety> <def>One of a class of fabled
female water spirits who might receive a human soul by intermarrying
with a mortal.</def><-- a water nymph -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

